00076 /*
00077  *  5-20-95
00078  *      Playdoh currently supports 3 models:
00079  *      1. v1-hp - Playdoh instruction set; with HP calling convention,
00080  *              parameter passing macros, data layout, stack layout, etc.
00081  *              Thus you can feed HP Lcode to playdoh but NOT HP Mcode (ie,
00082  *              code run thru phase1 of Lhppa).
00083  *      2. v1-sun - Playdoh instruction set; with Sparc calling convention,
00084  *              parameter passing macros, data layout, stack layout, etc.
00085  *              Thus you can feed Sparc Lcode to playdoh but NOT Sparc Mcode 
00086                 (ie, code run thru phase1 of Lsparc).
00087  *      3. v1.0 - This is purely configurable to any sort of calling 
00088  *              convention, data layout, stack layout that you desire.  
00089  *              Currently it is set up identical to HP-PA because we don't 
00090  *              have much originality.  Also the emulator operates on an HP 
00091  *              or Sparc, so if you ever want the code to run, you best use 
00092  *              one of those 2 platforms.
00093  *      If you have questions talk to Rick or Scott.
00094  *
00095  *  12-04
00096  *      Only the last model (v1.0) is currently supported
00097  */

00296 int
00297 M_playdoh_eval_type (M_Type type, M_Type ntype)
00298 {
00299   if (M_playdoh_model == M_PLAYDOH_V1)
00300     {
00301       switch (type->type)
00302         {
00303         case M_TYPE_VOID:
00304           M_playdoh_void (ntype);
00305           return (-1);          /* can not be evaluated */
00306         case M_TYPE_BIT_LONG:
00307         case M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR:
00308         case M_TYPE_CHAR:
00309         case M_TYPE_SHORT:
00310         case M_TYPE_INT:
00311         case M_TYPE_LONG:
00312         case M_TYPE_POINTER:
00313         case M_TYPE_BLOCK:
00314           /* the starting address of array is used */
00315           M_playdoh_int (ntype, type->unsign);
00316           return (M_TYPE_INT);
00317         case M_TYPE_LLONG:
00318           M_playdoh_llong (ntype, type->unsign);
00319           break;
00320         case M_TYPE_FLOAT:
00321           M_playdoh_float (ntype, type->unsign);
00322           return (M_TYPE_FLOAT);
00323         case M_TYPE_DOUBLE:
00324           M_playdoh_double (ntype, type->unsign);
00325           return (M_TYPE_DOUBLE);
00326         case M_TYPE_UNION:
00327         case M_TYPE_STRUCT:
00328           *ntype = *type;
00329           return type->type;
00330         default:
00331           return (-1);
00332         }
00333     }
00334   else
00335     {
00336       M_assert (0, "M_playdoh_eval_type: illegal machine model");
00337       return (0);
00338     }
00339 }

00595 int
00596 M_playdoh_union_size (int n, _M_Type * type)
00597 {
00598   if (M_playdoh_model == M_PLAYDOH_V1)
00599     {
00600       int i, aln, max_size, max_align;
00601 
00602       max_size = 0;
00603       max_align = 0;
00604       for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
00605         {
00606           int size;
00607           size = type[i].size;
00608           if (size > max_size)
00609             max_size = size;
00610           aln = type[i].align;
00611           if (aln > max_align)
00612             max_align = aln;
00613         }
00614 
00615       /*
00616        *      align to at least byte boundary.
00617        */
00618       if (max_align < M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_CHAR)
00619         max_align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_CHAR;
00620 
00621       /* need to increment to the max. align for future array extension */
00622       i = max_size % max_align;
00623       if (i != 0)
00624         max_size += (max_align - i);
00625 
00626       return max_size;
00627     }
00628   else
00629     {
00630       M_assert (0, "M_playdoh_union_size: illegal machine model");
00631       return (0);
00632     }

00635 void
00636 M_playdoh_struct_layout (int n, _M_Type * type, int *base, int *bit_offset)
00637 {
00638   if (M_playdoh_model == M_PLAYDOH_V1)
00639     {
00640       int i, offset;
00641       int mod, size, align, mod_word, mod_type;
00642 
00643       offset = 0;               /* assume initially aligned */
00644       for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
00645         {
00646           size = type[i].size;
00647           align = type[i].align;
00648           M_assert ((size != 0) && (align != 0),
00649                     "M_struct_layout: void is not allowed in structure");
00650           /*
00651            *  need to treat bit fields specially.
00652            *  keep them in a word when possible.
00653            */
00654           mod_word = offset % M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT;
00655           if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR)
00656             {
00657               if ((mod_word + size) > M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT)
00658                 offset += (M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00659               else
00660                 {
00661                   mod_type = offset % M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_CHAR;
00662                   if ((mod_type + size) > M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_CHAR)
00663                     {
00664                       type[i].type = M_TYPE_BIT_SHORT;
00665                     }
00666                 }
00667             }
00668           if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_SHORT)
00669             {
00670               if ((mod_word + size) > M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT)
00671                 offset += (M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00672               else
00673                 {
00674                   mod_type = offset % M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_SHORT;
00675                   if ((mod_type + size) > M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_SHORT)
00676                     {
00677                       type[i].type = M_TYPE_BIT_LONG;
00678                     }
00679                 }
00680             }
00681           else if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_LONG)
00682             {
00683               if ((mod_word + size) > M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT)
00684                 offset += (M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00685             }
00686           mod = offset % align; /* align to what the field */
00687           if (mod != 0)         /* needs to start from */
00688             offset += (align - mod);
00689 
00690           if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR)
00691             {
00692               int mod = offset % M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT;
00693 
00694               bit_offset[i] = offset - mod +
00695                 (M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT - mod - size);
00696               base[i] = offset & (~(M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_CHAR - 1));
00697             }
00698           else if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_SHORT)
00699             {
00700               int mod = offset % M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT;
00701 
00702               bit_offset[i] = offset - mod +
00703                 (M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT - mod - size);
00704               base[i] = offset & (~(M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_SHORT - 1));
00705 
00706             }
00707           else if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_LONG)
00708             {
00709               int mod = offset % M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT;
00710 
00711               bit_offset[i] = offset - mod +
00712                 (M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT - mod - size);
00713               base[i] = offset & (~(M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_LONG - 1));
00714             }
00715           else
00716             {
00717               base[i] = offset;
00718               bit_offset[i] = 0;
00719             }
00720 
00721           offset += size;       /* allocate space */
00722         }
00723     }
00724   else
00725     {
00726       M_assert (0, "M_playdoh_struct_layout: illegal machine model");
00727     }

00757 int
00758 M_playdoh_struct_size (int n, _M_Type * type, int struct_align)
00759 {
00760   if (M_playdoh_model == M_PLAYDOH_V1)
00761     {
00762       int i, offset;
00763       int mod, size, align, max_align, mod_word;
00764       offset = 0;               /* assume initially aligned */
00765       max_align = struct_align;
00766       for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
00767         {
00768           size = type[i].size;
00769           align = type[i].align;
00770           M_assert ((size != 0) && (align != 0),
00771                     "M_struct_layout: void is not allowed in structure");
00772           if (align > max_align)
00773             max_align = align;
00774           /*
00775            *  need to treat bit fields specially.
00776            *  keep them in a word when possible.
00777            */
00778           mod_word = offset % M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT;
00779           if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR)
00780             {
00781               if ((mod_word + size) > M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT)
00782                 offset += (M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00783               if (M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_CHAR > max_align)
00784                 max_align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_CHAR;
00785             }
00786           else if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_SHORT)
00787             {
00788               if ((mod_word + size) > M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT)
00789                 offset += (M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00790               if (M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_SHORT > max_align)
00791                 max_align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_SHORT;
00792             }
00793           else if (type[i].type == M_TYPE_BIT_LONG)
00794             {
00795               if ((mod_word + size) > M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT)
00796                 offset += (M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT - mod_word);
00797               if (M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_LONG > max_align)
00798                 max_align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_LONG;
00799             }
00800           mod = offset % align; /* align to what the field */
00801           if (mod != 0)         /* needs to start from */
00802             offset += (align - mod);
00803 
00804           offset += size;
00805         }
00806       /*
00807        * align to at least byte boundary.
00808        */
00809       if (max_align < M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_CHAR)
00810         max_align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_CHAR;
00811       /* enforce max. alignment */
00812       mod = offset % max_align;
00813       if (mod != 0)
00814         offset += (max_align - mod);
00815       return offset;
00816     }
00817   else
00818     {
00819       M_assert (0, "M_playdoh_struct_size: illegal machine model");
00820       return (0);
00821     }

00825 int
00826 M_playdoh_layout_fnvar (List param_list, char **base_macro, int *pcount,
00827                      int purpose)
00828 {
00829   M_Param param;
00830   int max_align, off;
00831   int int_rg;
00832   int fp_rg;
00833   int size, align, mod, tp;
00834 
00835 
00836   switch (purpose)
00837     {
00838     case M_GET_FNVAR:
00839       *base_macro = "$IP";
00840       break;
00841     case M_PUT_FNVAR:
00842       *base_macro = "$OP";
00843       break;
00844     case M_DONT_CARE_FNVAR:
00845     default:
00846       M_assert (0, "M_fnvar_layout: unknown purpose");
00847     }
00848 
00849   max_align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_MAX;
00850   fp_rg = 0;
00851   int_rg = 0;
00852   off = 0;
00853 
00854   List_start (param_list);
00855   while ((param = (M_Param)List_next (param_list)))
00856     {
00857       tp = param->mtype.type;
00858 
00859       switch (tp)
00860         {
00861         case M_TYPE_CHAR:
00862         case M_TYPE_SHORT:
00863         case M_TYPE_INT:
00864         case M_TYPE_LONG:
00865         case M_TYPE_POINTER:
00866           if (int_rg < M_PLAYDOH_MAX_FNVAR_REG)
00867             {
00868               param->mode = M_THRU_REGISTER;
00869               param->reg = (int_rg)++ + M_PLAYDOH_INT_BASE;
00870             }
00871           else
00872             {
00873               param->mode = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00874               param->reg = -1;
00875             }
00876           break;
00877 
00878         case M_TYPE_LLONG:
00879           if(int_rg + 1 < M_PLAYDOH_MAX_FNVAR_REG) {
00880             param->mode = M_THRU_REGISTER;
00881             param->reg = (int_rg) + M_PLAYDOH_INT_BASE;
00882             int_rg += 2;
00883           }
00884           else {
00885             param->mode = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00886             param->reg = -1;
00887             if(int_rg < M_PLAYDOH_MAX_FNVAR_REG)
00888               int_rg++;
00889           }
00890           break;
00891 
00892         case M_TYPE_FLOAT:
00893           if (int_rg < M_PLAYDOH_MAX_FNVAR_REG)
00894             {
00895               param->mode = M_THRU_REGISTER;
00896               param->reg = (fp_rg) + 1 + M_PLAYDOH_FLT_BASE;
00897               int_rg += 1;
00898               fp_rg  += 1;
00899             }
00900           else
00901             {
00902               param->mode = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00903               param->reg = -1;
00904             }
00905           break;
00906 
00907         case M_TYPE_DOUBLE:
00908           if (int_rg < M_PLAYDOH_MAX_FNVAR_REG)
00909             {
00910               param->mode = M_THRU_REGISTER;
00911               param->reg = fp_rg + 1 + M_PLAYDOH_FLT_BASE;
00912               int_rg += 2;
00913               fp_rg  += 1;
00914             }
00915           else
00916             {
00917               param->mode = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00918               param->reg = -1;
00919             }
00920           break;
00921 
00922         case M_TYPE_UNION:
00923         case M_TYPE_STRUCT:
00924           size = param->mtype.size;
00925           if (int_rg < M_PLAYDOH_MAX_FNVAR_REG)
00926             {
00927               param->mode = M_INDIRECT_THRU_REGISTER;
00928               param->reg = (int_rg)++ + M_PLAYDOH_INT_BASE;
00929             }
00930           else
00931             {
00932               if (size <= M_PLAYDOH_SMALL_STRUCT_MAX)
00933                 param->mode = M_THRU_MEMORY;
00934               else
00935                 param->mode = M_INDIRECT_THRU_MEMORY;
00936               param->reg = -1;
00937             }
00938           break;
00939         default:
00940           M_assert (0, "M_fnvar_layout: argument is not promoted");
00941         }
00942       /* note, the method of calculating offsets may seem strange, but */
00943       /* the PA convention has the stack growing towards high memory   */
00944       /* and the parameters are referenced back from the $sp, with the */
00945       /* first parameter being closest to the stack pointer            */
00946       size = param->mtype.size;
00947       align = param->mtype.align;
00948 
00949       if (param->mtype.type == M_TYPE_UNION || 
00950           param->mtype.type == M_TYPE_STRUCT)
00951         {
00952           /* make sure correct size and alignment is used for 
00953            * struct/union passed indirectly thru registers
00954            * if IMPACT allowed structures to be passed via registers, 
00955            * this would not have to be done                           
00956            */
00957           if (param->mode == M_INDIRECT_THRU_REGISTER)
00958             {
00959               size = M_PLAYDOH_SIZE_INT;
00960               align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_INT;
00961             }
00962         }
00963       if (align >= M_PLAYDOH_SMALL_STRUCT_MAX &&
00964           param->mtype.type != M_TYPE_DOUBLE)
00965         /* anything larger than a 64-bit structure is passed */
00966         /* indirectly thru memory                            */
00967         align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_INT;
00968       else if (align < M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_INT)
00969         /* anything smaller that 32-bits is passed as 32-bits */
00970         align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_INT;
00971 
00972       mod = off % align;
00973 
00974       /* place the offset pointer to the boundary of the appropriate */
00975       /* data size                                                   */
00976       if (mod != 0)
00977         off += (align - mod);
00978 
00979 #ifndef JWS_NEW_STACK_MODEL
00980       /* now increment the offset to point to the actual location    */
00981       /* for this parameter                                          */
00982       off += size;
00983       param->offset = -off;
00984 #else
00985       param->offset = off;
00986       off += size;
00987 #endif
00988     }
00989 
00990 
00991   /* The param section must be at least certain size.
00992    * This is the backing store for the parameter regs. */
00993   if (off < MIN_PARAM_SIZE)
00994     off = MIN_PARAM_SIZE;
00995 
00996   /* now for the body of the structures... small ones first. */
00997 
00998   List_start (param_list);
00999   while ((param = (M_Param)List_next (param_list)))
01000     {
01001       tp = param->mtype.type;
01002       size = param->mtype.size;
01003 
01004       if (((tp == M_TYPE_UNION) ||
01005            (tp == M_TYPE_STRUCT)) &&
01006           (size <= M_PLAYDOH_SMALL_STRUCT_MAX))
01007         {
01008 
01009           /* must align to a double boundry */
01010           align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_MAX;
01011 
01012           mod = off % align;
01013 
01014           if (mod != 0)
01015             off += (align - mod);
01016 
01017 #ifndef JWS_NEW_STACK_MODEL
01018           off += size;
01019           param->paddr = -off;
01020 #else
01021           param->paddr = off;
01022           off += size;
01023 #endif
01024         }
01025     }
01026   /* now large ones */
01027   List_start (param_list);
01028   while ((param = (M_Param)List_next (param_list)))
01029     {
01030       tp = param->mtype.type;
01031 
01032       size = param->mtype.size;
01033 
01034       if (((tp == M_TYPE_UNION) ||
01035            (tp == M_TYPE_STRUCT)) &&
01036           (size > M_PLAYDOH_SMALL_STRUCT_MAX))
01037         {
01038 
01039           /* must align to a double boundry */
01040           align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_MAX;
01041 
01042           mod = off % align;
01043 
01044           if (mod != 0)
01045             off += (align - mod);
01046 #ifndef JWS_NEW_STACK_MODEL
01047           off += size;
01048           param->paddr = -off;
01049 #else
01050           param->paddr = off;
01051           off += size;
01052 #endif
01053         }
01054     }
01055 
01056   *pcount = int_rg;
01057   return off;           /* the total size needed */
01058 }

01305           size = type[i].size;
01306 
01307           if (((tp == M_TYPE_UNION) ||
01308                (tp == M_TYPE_STRUCT)) &&
01309               (size <= M_PLAYDOH_SMALL_STRUCT_MAX))
01310             {
01311 
01312               /* must align to a double boundry */
01313               align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_MAX;
01314 
01315               mod = off % align;
01316 
01317               if (mod != 0)
01318                 off += (align - mod);
01319 
01320 #ifndef JWS_NEW_STACK_MODEL
01321               off += size;
01322               paddr[i] = -off;
01323 #else
01324               paddr[i] = off;
01325               off += size;
01326 #endif
01327             }
01328         }
01329       /* now large ones */
01330       for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
01331         {
01332           tp = type[i].type;
01333 
01334           size = type[i].size;
01335 
01336           if (((tp == M_TYPE_UNION) ||
01337                (tp == M_TYPE_STRUCT)) &&
01338               (size > M_PLAYDOH_SMALL_STRUCT_MAX))
01339             {
01340 
01341               /* must align to a double boundry */
01342               align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_MAX;
01343 
01344               mod = off % align;
01345 
01346               if (mod != 0)
01347                 off += (align - mod);
01348 #ifndef JWS_NEW_STACK_MODEL
01349               off += size;
01350               paddr[i] = -off;
01351 #else
01352               paddr[i] = off;
01353               off += size;
01354 #endif
01355             }
01356         }
01357 
01358       *pcount = int_rg;
01359       return off;               /* the total size needed */
01360 
01361     }
01362   else
01363     {
01364       M_assert (0, "M_playdoh_fnvar_layout: illegal machine model");
01365       return (0);
01366     }
01367 }

01369 /*--------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
01370 int
01371 M_playdoh_lvar_layout (int n, _M_Type * type, long int *offset,
01372                        char **base_macro)
01373 {
01374   if (M_playdoh_model == M_PLAYDOH_V1)
01375     {
01376       int i, max_align, off;
01377       int size, align, mod, tp;
01378       /*
01379        *      the LOCAL section must be max. aligned initially
01380        */
01381       max_align = M_PLAYDOH_ALIGN_MAX;
01382       off = 0;
01383       for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
01384         {
01385           tp = type[i].type;
01386           if (tp == M_TYPE_BIT_LONG)
01387             {
01388               M_assert (0, "M_lvar_layout: bit field not allowed");
01389             }
01390           if (tp == M_TYPE_BIT_CHAR)
01391             {
01392               M_assert (0, "M_lvar_layout: bit field not allowed");
01393             }
01394           size = type[i].size;
01395           align = type[i].align;
01396           mod = off % align;
01397           if (mod != 0)
01398             off += (align - mod);
01399           off += size;
01400           offset[i] = -off;
01401         }
01402 
01403       /* the local section must be max. aligned */
01404       mod = off % max_align;
01405       if (mod != 0)
01406         off += (max_align - mod);
01407       /*
01408        *      Local variables are relative to $LV
01409        */
01410       *base_macro = "$LV";
01411       return off;               /* the total size needed */
01412     }
01413   else
01414     {
01415       M_assert (0, "M_playdoh_lvar_layout: illegal machine model");
01416       return (0);
01417     }
01418 }

01475 int
01476 M_playdoh_is_jumptbl_label (char *label, char *fn, int *tbl_id)
01477 {
01478   if (M_playdoh_model == M_PLAYDOH_V1)
01479     {
01480       char *ptr;
01481       int label_len, fn_len, base_len;
01482 
01483       /* Check the prefix */
01484       if (strncmp (label, "_$", 2))
01485         return (0);
01486 
01487       /* Some length checks, to make sure we dont step outside array */
01488       label_len = strlen (label);
01489       fn_len = strlen (fn);
01490       base_len = strlen (M_JUMPTBL_BASE_NAME);
01491       if (label_len <= (2 + fn_len + base_len))
01492         return (0);
01493 
01494       /* Check that fn is correct */
01495       ptr = label;
01496       ptr += 2;
01497       if (strncmp (ptr, fn, fn_len))
01498         return (0);
01499 
01500       /* Check that jumptbl base name is correct */
01501       ptr += fn_len;
01502       if (strncmp (ptr, M_JUMPTBL_BASE_NAME, base_len))
01503         return (0);
01504 
01505       /* Get the id */
01506       ptr += base_len;
01507       return (sscanf (ptr, "%d", tbl_id) == 1);
01508     }
01509   else
01510     {
01511       M_assert (0, "M_playdoh_is_jumptbl_label: illegal machine model");
01512       return (0);
01513     }

03637 /*
03638  * Return true (1) if the instruction is supported in the hardware of the
03639  * processor.  Return false (0) otherwise.
03640  */
03641 int
03642 M_oper_supported_in_arch_playdoh (int opc)
03643 {
03644   if (M_playdoh_model == M_PLAYDOH_V1)
03645     {
03646       switch (opc)
03647         {
03648         case Lop_OR_NOT:
03649         case Lop_AND_NOT:
03650           return (0);
03651 
03652         case Lop_ABS:
03653         case Lop_NAND:
03654         case Lop_NOR:
03655         case Lop_NXOR:
03656         case Lop_AND_COMPL:
03657         case Lop_OR_COMPL:
03658         case Lop_ABS_F:
03659         case Lop_ABS_F2:
03660         case Lop_MUL_ADD_F:
03661         case Lop_MUL_ADD_F2:
03662         case Lop_MUL_SUB_F:
03663         case Lop_MUL_SUB_F2:
03664         case Lop_MUL_SUB_REV_F:
03665         case Lop_MUL_SUB_REV_F2:
03666         case Lop_SQRT_F:
03667         case Lop_SQRT_F2:
03668         case Lop_MIN_F:
03669         case Lop_MIN_F2:
03670         case Lop_MAX_F:
03671         case Lop_MAX_F2:
03672         case Lop_RCP_F:
03673         case Lop_RCP_F2:
03674           return (1);
03675 
03676         default:
03677           return (1);
03678         }
03679     }
03680   else
03681     {
03682       M_assert (0, "M_oper_supported_in_arch_playdoh: illegal machine model");
03683       return (0);
03684     }
03685 }

03687 /*
03688  * Returns the number of machine instructions required to implement the
03689  * specified oper in the best case.  It is assumed that this is for
03690  * supported instructions.  A call to M_oper_supported_in_arch should be
03691  * made for abnormal instructions.
03692  */
03693 int
03694 M_num_oper_required_for_playdoh (L_Oper * oper, char *name)
03695 {
03696 #define zero_offset(a)          ((a->src[1]->type==L_OPERAND_IMMED) &&\
03697                                  ((a->src[1]->ctype&0x30)==0x00)&&\

03718 
03719 #define short_int_inc(a,b)      ((a->src[b]->type==L_OPERAND_IMMED)&&\
03720                                  ((a->src[b]->ctype&0x30)==0x00)&&\
03721                                  (a->src[b]->value.i >= -0x10) &&\
03722                                  (a->src[b]->value.i < 0x10))

03724                                  ((a->src[b]->ctype&0x30)==0x00)&&\
03725                                  (a->src[b]->value.i > 0) && \
03726                                  (a->src[b]->value.i < 0x2000))

03729                                  (a->src[b]->value.i >= -0x2000) && \
03730                                  (a->src[b]->value.i < 0))
03731 #define register_inc(a,b)        (a->src[b]->type == L_OPERAND_REGISTER)
03732       switch (oper->opc)
03733         {
03734         case Lop_ST_C:
03735         case Lop_ST_C2:
03736         case Lop_ST_I:
03737         case Lop_ST_Q:

03739             return (2);

03741             return (1);
03742

03744         case Lop_LD_C:

03750             return (2);
03751           else
03752             return (1);
03753 
03754         case Lop_ST_F:
03755         case Lop_ST_F2:
03756           if (indexed_memory_op (oper) || has_label_operand (oper))
03757             return (2);
03758           else
03759             return (1);
03760 
03761         case Lop_LD_F:
03762         case Lop_LD_F2:
03763           if (indexed_memory_op (oper) || has_label_operand (oper))
03764             return (2);
03765           else
03766             return (1);
03767 
03768         case Lop_LD_POST_UC:
03769         case Lop_LD_POST_C:
03770         case Lop_LD_POST_UC2:
03771         case Lop_LD_POST_C2:
03772         case Lop_LD_POST_I:
03773         case Lop_LD_POST_Q:
03774           if (non_zero_offset (oper))
03775             return (2);
03776           else if (short_int_inc (oper, 2) ||
03777                    long_pos_int_inc (oper, 2) || register_inc (oper, 2))
03778             return (1);
03779           else
03780             return (2);
03781 
03782         case Lop_ST_POST_C:
03783         case Lop_ST_POST_C2:
03784         case Lop_ST_POST_I:
03785         case Lop_ST_POST_Q:
03786           if (indexed_memory_op (oper) || non_zero_offset (oper))
03787             return (2);
03788           else if (short_int_inc (oper, 3) || long_pos_int_inc (oper, 3))
03789             return (1);
03790           else
03791             return (2);

03794         case Lop_LD_POST_F2:

03796             return (2);
03797           else if (short_int_inc (oper, 2) || register_inc (oper, 2))
03798             return (1);
03799           else
03800             return (2);
03801 
03802         case Lop_ST_POST_F:
03803         case Lop_ST_POST_F2:
03804           if (non_zero_offset (oper))

03808           else

03817         case Lop_LD_PRE_UC:

03934 /* Mechanism for playdoh to specify the offset between the left float
03935  * register numer and the double register number.  Typically, this
03936  * offset should be set to num_flt_callee_reg in playdoh. -JCG 6/99
03937  */
03938 int M_playdoh_dbl_offset = 0;
03939 
03940 /* Conflicting operand functions for impact ver1 and hppa models */
03941 /*
03942  *      Structure of assumed register file for IMPACT machine, so this
03943  *      is what is used after register allocation for the IMPACT machine
03944  *
03945  *      int registers
03946  *              1
03947  *              ...
03948  *              playdoh_num_int_reg (required to be an even #)
03949  *
03950  *      flt/dbl registers (double == consecective float regs)
03951  *      (double reg number is left float + M_playdoh_dbl_offset -JCG 6/99)
03952  *              playdoh_num_int_reg+1   playdoh_num_int_reg+2
03953  *              ...                     ...
03954  *              playdoh_num_flt_reg+M_playdoh_dbl_offset-1   
03955  *              playdoh_num_flt_reg+M_playdoh_dbl_offset
03956  *      Note: Doubles use only odd register numbers after allocation! -JCG 6/99
03957  *
03958  *      prd registrs
03959  *              playdoh_num_flt_reg
03960  *              ...
03961  *              playdoh_num_prd_reg
03962  *
03963  *      Return registers:
03964  *              P0 (int), P2 (dbl) (no flt and prd parameter passing regs)
03965  *              --> actually P1 is flt, but should never see!!!
03966  *
03967  *      Parameter passing
03968  *              P4-P7 (int), P12-P15(dbl) 
03969  *              (no flt and prd parameter passing regs)
03970  *              --> actually P8-P11 is flt, but should never see!!!
03971  *
03972  *      Stack ptr, Frame ptr
03973  *              SP, FP
03974  *
03975  *      Note for now, handle all macros so can run playdoh on all Lcodes
03976  *      for any target machine.
03977  */
03978 
03979 int
03980 M_conflicting_operands_playdoh (L_Operand * operand,
03981                                 L_Operand ** conflict_array, int len,
03982                                 int prepass)
03983 {
03984   if (M_playdoh_model == M_PLAYDOH_V1) {
03985     int i = 0;
03986 
03987     /* Use this case if no register allocation has been done on the code!! */
03988     if (prepass)
03989       {
03990         if (L_is_reg (operand))
03991           {
03992             conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
03993           }
03994         else if (L_is_macro (operand))
03995           {
03996             conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
03997           }
03998         else
03999           {
04000             M_assert (0,
04001                       "playdoh_conflicting_operands: illegal operand type "
04002                       "(no regalloc)");
04003           }
04004       }
04005 
04006     /* else register allocation has been done */
04007     else if (L_is_reg (operand))
04008       {
04009         /* int register */
04010         if (L_is_ctype_integer (operand))
04011           {
04012             conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
04013           }
04014         /* Made match playdoh's register bank definitions -JCG 6/99 */
04015         else if (L_is_ctype_dbl (operand))
04016           {
04017             /* Sanity check, double register operand number must be odd
04018              * after register allocation!
04019              */
04020             if ((operand->value.r & 0x1) == 0)
04021               {
04022                 M_assert (0,
04023                           "playdoh_conflicting_operands: "
04024                           "illegal even double regsiter after regalloc!");
04025               }
04026 
04027             /* Set up conflicting double register */
04028             conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
04029 
04030             /* Set up conflicting float registers. */
04031             /* Left float reg # + M_playdoh_dbl_offset  = double reg # */
04032             conflict_array[i] = L_copy_operand (operand);
04033             conflict_array[i]->ctype = L_CTYPE_FLOAT;
04034             conflict_array[i++]->value.r =
04035               operand->value.r - M_playdoh_dbl_offset;
04036 
04037             /* Right float reg # + M_playdoh_dbl_offset - 1 = double reg # */
04038             conflict_array[i] = L_copy_operand (operand);
04039             conflict_array[i]->ctype = L_CTYPE_FLOAT;
04040             conflict_array[i++]->value.r =
04041               (operand->value.r - M_playdoh_dbl_offset) + 1;
04042 
04043 #if 0
04044             /* Debug */
04045             fprintf (stderr, "For operand: ");
04046             L_print_operand (stderr, operand, 1);
04047             fprintf (stderr, "\nConflict array: ");
04048             L_print_operand (stderr, conflict_array[0], 1);
04049             L_print_operand (stderr, conflict_array[1], 1);
04050             L_print_operand (stderr, conflict_array[2], 1);
04051             fprintf (stderr, "\n\n");
04052 #endif
04053           }
04054         /* Made match playdoh's register bank definitions -JCG 6/99 */
04055         else if (L_is_ctype_flt (operand))
04056           {
04057             /* If left register */
04058             if (operand->value.r & 0x1)
04059               {
04060                 /* Set up conflicting float register */
04061                 conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
04062 
04063                 /* Set up conflicting double register */
04064                 /* Left float reg # + M_playdoh_dbl_offset  = double reg # */
04065                 conflict_array[i] = L_copy_operand (operand);
04066                 conflict_array[i]->ctype = L_CTYPE_DOUBLE;
04067                 conflict_array[i++]->value.r =
04068                   operand->value.r + M_playdoh_dbl_offset;
04069 
04070 #if 0
04071                 /* Debug */
04072                 fprintf (stderr, "For operand: ");
04073                 L_print_operand (stderr, operand, 1);
04074                 fprintf (stderr, "\nConflict array: ");
04075                 L_print_operand (stderr, conflict_array[0], 1);
04076                 L_print_operand (stderr, conflict_array[1], 1);
04077                 fprintf (stderr, "\n\n");
04078 #endif
04079               }
04080             else
04081               {
04082                 /* Set up conflicting float register */
04083                 conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
04084 
04085                 /* Set up conflicting double register */
04086                 /* Right float reg # + M_playdoh_dbl_offset - 1 =double reg # */
04087                 conflict_array[i] = L_copy_operand (operand);
04088                 conflict_array[i]->ctype = L_CTYPE_DOUBLE;
04089                 conflict_array[i++]->value.r =
04090                   operand->value.r + M_playdoh_dbl_offset - 1;
04091 
04092 #if 0
04093                 /* Debug */
04094                 fprintf (stderr, "For operand: ");
04095                 L_print_operand (stderr, operand, 1);
04096                 fprintf (stderr, "\nConflict array: ");
04097                 L_print_operand (stderr, conflict_array[0], 1);
04098                 L_print_operand (stderr, conflict_array[1], 1);
04099                 fprintf (stderr, "\n\n");
04100 #endif
04101               }
04102           }
04103 #if 1
04104         else if (L_MAC_PRED_ALL)
04105           {
04106             int j, num_preds, pred_base;
04107 
04108             conflict_array[i++] =
04109               L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_PRED_ALL, L_CTYPE_PREDICATE,
04110                                    L_PTYPE_NULL);
04111 
04112             num_preds = Mspec_num_prd_callee_reg;
04113             pred_base = (Mspec_num_int_caller_reg +
04114                          Mspec_num_int_callee_reg + 
04115                          Mspec_num_flt_caller_reg*2 +
04116                          Mspec_num_flt_callee_reg*2);
04117             for (j = 0; j < num_preds; j++)
04118               {
04119                 conflict_array[i++] =
04120                   L_new_register_operand (pred_base + j,
04121                                           L_CTYPE_PREDICATE, 
04122                                           L_PTYPE_NULL);
04123               }
04124           }
04125 #endif
04126         /* pred register */
04127         else if (L_is_ctype_predicate (operand))
04128           {
04129             conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
04130 #if 1
04131             conflict_array[i++] = L_new_macro_operand (L_MAC_PRED_ALL, 
04132                                                        L_CTYPE_PREDICATE,
04133                                                        L_PTYPE_NULL);
04134 #endif
04135           }
04136         else
04137           {
04138             M_assert (0, "playdoh_conflicting_operands: illegal reg number");
04139           }
04140       }
04141     else if (L_is_macro (operand))
04142       {
04143         conflict_array[i++] = L_copy_operand (operand);
04144       }
04145     else
04146       {
04147         printf("%d %d\n",i,len);
04148         M_assert (0, "M_conflicting_operands_playdoh: unsupported operand\n");
04149       }
04150 
04151     if (i > len)
04152       {
04153         printf("%d %d\n",i,len);
04154         M_assert (0,"M_conflicting_operands_playdoh: too many conflicts\n");
04155       }
04156 
04157     return (i);
04158   }
04159   else
04160     {
04161       M_assert (0, "M_conflicting_operands_playdoh: illegal machine model");
04162       return (0);
04163     }
04164 }
